Please ensure you have docker installed on your system
check if you have docker-compose installed with docker-compose -v
otherwise install on your terminal with the following command - curl -L https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/download/1.18.0/docker-compose-`uname -s`-`uname -m` -o /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
set permissions with  chmod +x /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
You may also need to confirm you have node installed incase you don't with this command node -v
if absent, use sudo apt-get install node // this will install node and npm 
Navigate to your preferred directory on the terminal and clone the project from https://github.com/mordernGeek/UserManager
move to UserManager folder - cd UserManager from the terminal 
type the following command
docker-compose up // this will automatically create 2 containers dmongo and expresso from the compose file and the dockerfile in this directory
and link them up.
We are up!


